				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drclef" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(213153); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=213153&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205252" alt="DrClef" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=213153)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drclef" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(213153); return false;" >DrClef</a></span> <span class="odate time_1245084056 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">15 Jun 2009 16:40</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-509472">
									

<p>Okay, let me address this.</p>
<p>1. Dr. Kain being turned into a dog is not presented as a good thing, but as another bizarre circumstance caused by an accident working at the Foundation.</p>
<p>2. Clef does not have a spider for a head. Nor is his cock a hand. His head LOOKS like a spider in official documents because he's packed full of weird-ass anti-intrusion technology from his old job.</p>
<p>The others are SCP articles.</p>
<p>Now, what is the difference between these two things and your Symbiote?</p>
<p>Answer: they are asides. They are touched on and then ignored. They are simply one more aspect to the character, not the be-all and end-all of the character.</p>
<p>Read Dr. Kain's profile:</p>
<p><em>His most notable exploit was [DATA EXPUNGED], in which he was turned into a dog.</em></p>
<p>Boom. One sentence. That's it.</p>
<p>Read my profile:</p>
<p><em>A. Clef's true face cannot be clearly photographed by any known means (see above), but appears to have a sizable nose and a large grin resembling that of Felis cheshiricus, the only known specimen of which was captured by [DATA EXPUNGED] during Operation Liddell.</em></p>
<p>Boom. Not even one sentence. One clause IN a sentence.</p>
<p>If you'd presented the symbiote as, "Well, it somehow got attached to him, just another day at the Foundation," maybe it wouldn't be such a big deal, but you've basically made it half your character profile. Which seems a lot like Mary Suing it up.</p>
<p>But what the hell do I know, right?</p>

							</div>

								
					
