														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-509690">
									

<p>Wait, you have <em>illusionary powers</em>?</p>
<p>Well, I don't mind crazy user profiles. Agent Spoon can be a spoon all he wants, Senior Staff can be as wacky or mysterious as they desire. What I personally worry about, and treat this with as little gravity as you like, is this tendency towards the fun and exciting spilling over into the SCP list, and, to a lesser extent, the stories. Sure, we can have users who call themselves "Agent Spoon" or "Agent NekoChris". But it irks me to see these names crop up in what is the closest thing we have to canon. One example is the list of 914/261/978 experiments, which everybody, it seems, feels the need to sign with their name, no matter how weird or unlikely it is. If I write a test, I sure won't sign it Dr. Unimport, because Unimport is not an actual surname and I wouldn't be able to take myself seriously if I did so.</p>
<p>…well, feel free to ignore what I think. This is just a viewpoint on the matter from someone who loves to provide them at every opportunity.</p>
<p>Also, help yourself to my personal supplies of Internet Rage-Inducing Ecstasy, the perfect complement to any Internet Rave Party.</p>

