															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nekochris" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(283372); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=283372&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205252" alt="NekoChris" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=283372)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nekochris" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(283372); return false;" >NekoChris</a></span> <span class="odate time_1245099715 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">15 Jun 2009 21:01</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-509725">
									

<p>I enjoy detail. I enjoy fleshing things out. That's why it's not just a 'Oh hay there's this thing'. I want it to be more interesting than that. Interesting requires description requires detail requires in-depth explanations. I feel like if I just go 'Oh there's this thing too' people will say 'OH WELL TELL US MORE ABOUT THAT' and it will lead to 'THAT COMPLETELY NEGATES THE PREVIOUS SERIES OF COMPLAINTS'.</p>
<p>It didn't even START OUT as an SCP, it was completely contained to the profile, and somehow THAT set off ire. So I started writing a separate SCP for it at someone's behest and THAT set off ire. There is absolutely no sense of conformity for it so you know what? Fuck it.</p>
<p>I had intended to rewrite this anyway, so what I'm going to do, and already have done, is write up the entity as an SCP and leave it somewhere off the main highway. I'm going to write the profile from the point of an explantive, employee profile, that somebody might pull out of a file cabinet when information about a specific employee is required, and then I'm going to</p>
